/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_46.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Perhaps it had been better to leave it, since
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_460.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|There was nothing to be done, except wait for the morning.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_463.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Such search as could be made told them nothing.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_466.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The oxen had gone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_467.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"What was to be done?"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_468.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he asked.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_469.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|One said this thing,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_470.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but all agreed that they must wait to act until the snow melted.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_475.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Or till we freeze, you whose mothers were fools!"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_478.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|said the White Man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_479.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who was in the worst of tempers,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_481.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|He was the driver of the first wagon.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_483.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"My father,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_484.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he said to the White Man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_485.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|this is my word.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_487.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|The oxen are lost in the snow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_488.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|No man knows whither they have gone,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_49.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"Death chooses for himself,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_490.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|or whether they live or are now but hides and bones.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_493.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and he pointed to some huts about two miles away on the hillside,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_497.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the White Man.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_498.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Before him was a very ancient man,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_5.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|his servant,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_500.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|a mere bag of bones,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_501.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|with sightless eyes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_503.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and one hand-his left-white and shrivelled.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_506.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|asked the old man in a thin voice.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_508.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Yet I will do it,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_509.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though it is against your law,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_51.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and after all there was killing-of our own people,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_511.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and you do wrong to ask me,-yes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_514.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I will help you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_515.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|My father, I know what you seek.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_517.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You seek to know where your oxen have run for shelter from the cold!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_521.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|"It is so, Doctor,"
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_522.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|answered the White Man.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_523.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You have long ears.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_525.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have long ears,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_526.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|though they say that I grow deaf.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_528.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I have keen eyes also, and yet I cannot see your face.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_532.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Let me hearken!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_534.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Let me look!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_535.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You have a farm, White Man, down near Pine Town, is it not?
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_539.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you shall find your oxen-yes,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_54.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But in those days we did not guess what we should live to see,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_541.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|the little red Zulu ox with one horn,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_544.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You shall not find these, for they have died in the snow.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_548.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Send, and you will find the others.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_549.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I ask no fee!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_551.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|I do not work wonders for reward.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_553.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Now the White Man scoffed.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_555.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|But in the end, so great is the power of superstition, he sent.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_559.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|those whom he sent returned with the oxen,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_561.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|except the three only.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_563.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|After that he scoffed no more.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_565.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and every afternoon he came and talked with him,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_568.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|sitting far into the night.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_569.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|of whom he had let fall some words.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_57.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|it will be forgotten,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_572.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Then the old man told him the tale that is set out here.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_575.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Day by day he told some of it till it was finished.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_578.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It is not all written in these pages,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_58.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Only your name will not be forgotten;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_580.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Was the death of a warrior in question,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_583.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|he stabbed with his stick,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_584.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|showing how the blow fell and where;
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_586.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|did the story grow sorrowful, he groaned, or even wept.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_590.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Moreover, he had many voices, one for each of the actors in his tale.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_595.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|This man, ancient and withered, seemed to live again in the far past.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_599.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|It was the past that spoke to his listener,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_6.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|who slew him with the Princes.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_60.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|as it was heard in life so it shall be heard in story,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_64.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|however humbly,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_65.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|mine may pass down with it.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_67.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|and I must leave the ways of action that I love and bury myself in books,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_71.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|but the old days and friends are in my mind,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_74.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|nor while I have memory shall I forget them and you.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_77.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Elephant that is not turned!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_79.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You who nursed us from of old!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_8.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|you have crowned their kings and shared their counsels,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_81.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|You who overshadowed all peoples and took charge of them,
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_85.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|Help of the fatherless when in trouble!
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_87.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|PREFACE The writer of this romance has been encouraged to his task by a purpose somewhat beyond that of setting out a wild tale of savage life.
/mnt/data/home/aa2249/FYP/HiFi-TTS/10min/6097_96.wav|HiFi_Speaker|en|When he was yet a lad,-now some seventeen years ago,-fortune took him to South Africa.
